The paper deals with the optimization of deep neural networks, which is a central topic in machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on the impact of permutation symmetry on the loss landscape of deep networks. This topic is closely related to the fields of deep learning (cs.LG), neural networks (cs.NE), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper introduces a geometric approach to studying the loss landscape, which is related to the field of control theory (cs.SY).
